## ğŸ“‹ Prerequisites

Before you begin, ensure you have the following installed:

- **Node.js** >= 24.11.0 ([Download](https://nodejs.org/))
- **npm** >= 10.0.0 (comes with Node.js)
- **Docker** >= 20.10.0 ([Download](https://www.docker.com/))
- **Docker Compose** >= 2.0.0
- **Git** ([Download](https://git-scm.com/))

Optional but recommended:

- **pgAdmin** (included in Docker Compose)
- **Postman** or **Insomnia** for API testing

## ğŸš€ Quick Start

### 1ï¸âƒ£ Clone the Repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/YngJesus/StudyMateAI.git
cd StudyMateAI
```

### 2ï¸âƒ£ Environment Configuration

Create a `.env` file in the `backend` directory:

```env
# Database Configuration
DATABASE_HOST=localhost
DATABASE_PORT=5432
DATABASE_USER=postgres
DATABASE_PASSWORD=postgres
DATABASE_NAME=studymate

# JWT Configuration
JWT_SECRET=your-super-secret-jwt-key-change-in-production-min-32-chars
JWT_EXPIRES_IN=7d

# Groq AI Configuration
GROQ_API_KEY=your-groq-api-key-here
GROQ_MODEL=llama-3.3-70b-versatile

# Application Configuration
PORT=3000
NODE_ENV=development
CORS_ORIGIN=http://localhost:4200

# File Upload Configuration
MAX_FILE_SIZE=10485760  # 10MB in bytes
UPLOAD_PATH=./uploads
```

> ğŸ’¡ **Tip**: Get your free Groq API key at [console.groq.com](https://console.groq.com/)

### 3ï¸âƒ£ Start Docker Services

```bash
# Start PostgreSQL and pgAdmin
docker-compose up -d

# Verify services are running
docker-compose ps
```

### 4ï¸âƒ£ Backend Setup

```bash
cd backend

# Install dependencies
npm install

# Run database migrations
npm run migration:run

# Seed initial data (optional)
npm run seed

# Start development server
npm run start:dev
```

The backend will be available at `http://localhost:3000`

### 5ï¸âƒ£ Frontend Setup

```bash
# Open a new terminal
cd frontend

# Install dependencies
npm install

# Start development server
npm start
```

The frontend will be available at `http://localhost:4200`

### 6ï¸âƒ£ Access the Application

| Service          | URL                            | Credentials               |
| ---------------- | ------------------------------ | ------------------------- |
| **Frontend App** | http://localhost:4200          | Create account via signup |
| **Backend API**  | http://localhost:3000/api      | -                         |
| **Swagger Docs** | http://localhost:3000/api/docs | -                         |
| **pgAdmin**      | http://localhost:5050          | admin@admin.com / admin   |

### 7ï¸âƒ£ Default Test Account (After Seeding)

```
Email: test@studymate.com
Password: Test123!
```

## ğŸ“š API Documentation

### Interactive Documentation

Comprehensive API documentation is available via **Swagger UI** at:

- **Development**: http://localhost:3000/api/docs
- **Production**: https://your-domain.com/api/docs

### Authentication

All protected endpoints require a JWT token in the Authorization header:

```http
Authorization: Bearer <your-jwt-token>
```

### API Endpoints Overview

<details>
<summary><b>ğŸ” Authentication</b></summary>

```http
POST   /api/auth/signup          # Register new user
POST   /api/auth/login           # Login user
POST   /api/auth/refresh         # Refresh access token
GET    /api/auth/profile         # Get current user
PATCH  /api/auth/profile         # Update profile
```

**Example Request:**

```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/login \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"email":"user@example.com","password":"password123"}'
```

</details>

<details>
<summary><b>ğŸ“š Subjects & Courses</b></summary>

```http
GET    /api/subjects              # List all subjects
POST   /api/subjects              # Create new subject
GET    /api/subjects/:id          # Get subject details
PATCH  /api/subjects/:id          # Update subject
DELETE /api/subjects/:id          # Delete subject

GET    /api/courses               # List all courses
POST   /api/courses               # Create new course
GET    /api/courses/:id           # Get course details
GET    /api/courses/subject/:id   # Get courses by subject
PATCH  /api/courses/:id           # Update course
DELETE /api/courses/:id           # Delete course
```

</details>

<details>
<summary><b>ğŸ“„ PDF Management</b></summary>

```http
POST   /api/pdfs/upload           # Upload PDF document
GET    /api/pdfs                  # List all PDFs
GET    /api/pdfs/:id              # Get PDF details
GET    /api/pdfs/course/:id       # Get PDFs by course
GET    /api/pdfs/:id/download     # Download PDF
PATCH  /api/pdfs/:id              # Update PDF metadata
DELETE /api/pdfs/:id              # Delete PDF
```

**Upload Example:**

```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:3000/api/pdfs/upload \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer <token>" \
  -F "file=@document.pdf" \
  -F "courseId=123" \
  -F "tags=exam,chapter1"
```

</details>

<details>
<summary><b>ğŸ¤– AI Chat</b></summary>

```http
GET    /api/chat/sessions         # List all chat sessions
POST   /api/chat/sessions         # Create new session
GET    /api/chat/sessions/:id     # Get session details
PATCH  /api/chat/sessions/:id     # Update session title
DELETE /api/chat/sessions/:id     # Delete session

GET    /api/chat/history/:id      # Get chat messages
POST   /api/chat/:sessionId       # Send message to AI
DELETE /api/chat/message/:id      # Delete message
```

**Chat Request:**

```json
{
  "message": "Explain quantum physics",
  "pdfId": "optional-pdf-id-for-context"
}
```

</details>

<details>
<summary><b>ğŸ“… Calendar & Events</b></summary>

```http
GET    /api/events                # List all events
POST   /api/events                # Create event
GET    /api/events/:id            # Get event details
GET    /api/events/upcoming       # Get upcoming events
GET    /api/events/past           # Get past events
PATCH  /api/events/:id            # Update event
DELETE /api/events/:id            # Delete event
```

**Event Types:**

- `exam` - Examinations
- `assignment` - Assignments and homework
- `ds` - Directed Study sessions
</details>

<details>
<summary><b>ğŸ”” Notifications</b></summary>

```http
GET    /api/notifications                  # List all notifications
GET    /api/notifications/unread           # Get unread notifications
PATCH  /api/notifications/:id/read         # Mark as read
PATCH  /api/notifications/read-all         # Mark all as read
DELETE /api/notifications/:id              # Delete notification
POST   /api/notifications/cron/trigger     # Manual cron trigger (dev)
```

**WebSocket Connection:**

```javascript
const socket = io("http://localhost:3000", {
  auth: { token: "your-jwt-token" },
});

socket.on("notification", (data) => {
  console.log("New notification:", data);
});
```

</details>

<details>
<summary><b>ğŸ“Š Dashboard</b></summary>

```http
GET    /api/dashboard/stats       # Get overview statistics
GET    /api/dashboard/activity    # Get recent activity
GET    /api/dashboard/upcoming    # Get upcoming events
```

</details>

## ğŸ”§ Development

### Backend Development Commands

```bash
cd backend

# Development with hot-reload
npm run start:dev

# Production build
npm run build

# Production mode
npm run start:prod

# Run unit tests
npm run test

# Run e2e tests
npm run test:e2e

# Test coverage
npm run test:cov

# Linting
npm run lint

# Format code
npm run format
```

### Database Migrations

```bash
# Generate new migration
npm run migration:generate -- -n MigrationName

# Create empty migration
npm run migration:create -- -n MigrationName

# Run pending migrations
npm run migration:run

# Revert last migration
npm run migration:revert

# Show migration status
npm run migration:show
```

### Frontend Development Commands

```bash
cd frontend

# Development server (http://localhost:4200)
npm start

# Production build
npm run build

# Build with AOT compilation
npm run build:prod

# Run unit tests
npm test

# Run e2e tests
npm run e2e

# Linting
npm run lint

# Code formatting
npm run format
```

### Code Quality Tools

```bash
# Run all checks before commit
npm run pre-commit

# Type checking
npm run type-check

# Bundle analysis
npm run analyze
```

## ğŸ§ª Testing

### Backend Testing

```bash
