## ğŸ“¦ Production Deployment

### Environment Variables for Production

```env
# Backend .env.production
NODE_ENV=production
PORT=3000
DATABASE_HOST=your-db-host
DATABASE_PORT=5432
DATABASE_USER=your-db-user
DATABASE_PASSWORD=your-secure-password
DATABASE_NAME=studymate_prod
DATABASE_SSL=true

JWT_SECRET=your-very-secure-jwt-secret-min-64-chars
JWT_EXPIRES_IN=7d

GROQ_API_KEY=your-production-groq-key
GROQ_MODEL=llama-3.3-70b-versatile

CORS_ORIGIN=https://your-frontend-domain.com
```

### Backend Deployment

#### Option 1: Traditional Server

```bash
cd backend

# Install production dependencies only
npm ci --production

# Build the application
npm run build

# Run database migrations
npm run migration:run

# Start with PM2
pm2 start dist/main.js --name studymate-api

# Enable auto-restart on boot
pm2 startup
pm2 save
```

#### Option 2: Docker

```bash
# Build production image
docker build -t studymate-backend:latest ./backend

# Run container
docker run -d \
  --name studymate-api \
  -p 3000:3000 \
  --env-file .env.production \
  studymate-backend:latest
```

### Frontend Deployment

```bash
cd frontend

# Build for production with AOT
npm run build:prod

# Output will be in dist/frontend/browser
```

#### Deploy to Popular Platforms

<details>
<summary><b>Vercel</b></summary>

```bash
# Install Vercel CLI
npm i -g vercel

# Deploy
cd frontend
vercel --prod
```

</details>

<details>
<summary><b>Netlify</b></summary>

```bash
# Install Netlify CLI
npm i -g netlify-cli

# Deploy
cd frontend
npm run build:prod
netlify deploy --prod --dir=dist/frontend/browser
```

</details>

<details>
<summary><b>AWS S3 + CloudFront</b></summary>

```bash
# Build
npm run build:prod

# Sync to S3
aws s3 sync dist/frontend/browser s3://your-bucket-name

# Invalidate CloudFront cache
aws cloudfront create-invalidation \
  --distribution-id YOUR_DIST_ID \
  --paths "/*"
```

</details>

### Docker Compose Production

```bash
# Build and start all services
docker-compose -f docker-compose.prod.yml up -d

# View logs
docker-compose -f docker-compose.prod.yml logs -f

# Stop services
docker-compose -f docker-compose.prod.yml down
```

### Health Checks

```bash
# Check backend health
curl http://your-domain.com/api/health

# Check database connection
curl http://your-domain.com/api/health/db
```

