                      â””â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”˜
      â–²
      â”‚
      â”‚
â”Œâ”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”
â”‚Notificationsâ”‚
â””â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”˜
```

### Core Tables

#### **users**

| Column    | Type      | Description                |
| --------- | --------- | -------------------------- |
| id        | UUID      | Primary key                |
| email     | VARCHAR   | Unique email address       |
| password  | VARCHAR   | Hashed password (bcrypt)   |
| fullName  | VARCHAR   | User's full name           |
| role      | ENUM      | User role (admin, student) |
| createdAt | TIMESTAMP | Account creation date      |
| updatedAt | TIMESTAMP | Last update timestamp      |

#### **subjects**

| Column    | Type      | Description           |
| --------- | --------- | --------------------- |
| id        | UUID      | Primary key           |
| name      | VARCHAR   | Subject name          |
| color     | VARCHAR   | Hex color code for UI |
| userId    | UUID      | Foreign key to users  |
| createdAt | TIMESTAMP | Creation timestamp    |

#### **courses**

| Column      | Type      | Description             |
| ----------- | --------- | ----------------------- |
| id          | UUID      | Primary key             |
| name        | VARCHAR   | Course name             |
| description | TEXT      | Course description      |
| subjectId   | UUID      | Foreign key to subjects |
| createdAt   | TIMESTAMP | Creation timestamp      |

#### **pdfs**

| Column     | Type      | Description            |
| ---------- | --------- | ---------------------- |
| id         | UUID      | Primary key            |
| fileName   | VARCHAR   | Original file name     |
| filePath   | VARCHAR   | Storage path           |
| fileSize   | INTEGER   | File size in bytes     |
| courseId   | UUID      | Foreign key to courses |
| tags       | JSON      | Metadata tags array    |
| uploadedAt | TIMESTAMP | Upload timestamp       |

#### **chat_sessions**

| Column    | Type      | Description            |
| --------- | --------- | ---------------------- |
| id        | UUID      | Primary key            |
| title     | VARCHAR   | Session title          |
| userId    | UUID      | Foreign key to users   |
| createdAt | TIMESTAMP | Creation timestamp     |
| updatedAt | TIMESTAMP | Last message timestamp |

#### **chat_history**

| Column    | Type      | Description                  |
| --------- | --------- | ---------------------------- |
| id        | UUID      | Primary key                  |
| sessionId | UUID      | Foreign key to chat_sessions |
| message   | TEXT      | User message                 |
| response  | TEXT      | AI response                  |
| pdfId     | UUID      | Optional PDF context         |
| createdAt | TIMESTAMP | Message timestamp            |

#### **events**

| Column      | Type      | Description             |
| ----------- | --------- | ----------------------- |
| id          | UUID      | Primary key             |
| title       | VARCHAR   | Event title             |
| type        | ENUM      | exam, assignment, ds    |
| date        | DATE      | Event date              |
| description | TEXT      | Event details           |
| subjectId   | UUID      | Foreign key to subjects |
| userId      | UUID      | Foreign key to users    |
| createdAt   | TIMESTAMP | Creation timestamp      |

#### **notifications**

| Column    | Type      | Description            |
| --------- | --------- | ---------------------- |
| id        | UUID      | Primary key            |
| userId    | UUID      | Foreign key to users   |
| title     | VARCHAR   | Notification title     |
| message   | TEXT      | Notification content   |
| type      | ENUM      | urgent, warning, info  |
| isRead    | BOOLEAN   | Read status            |
| eventId   | UUID      | Optional related event |
| createdAt | TIMESTAMP | Creation timestamp     |

### Indexes

```sql
-- Performance optimization indexes
CREATE INDEX idx_users_email ON users(email);
CREATE INDEX idx_subjects_userId ON subjects(userId);
CREATE INDEX idx_courses_subjectId ON courses(subjectId);
CREATE INDEX idx_pdfs_courseId ON pdfs(courseId);
CREATE INDEX idx_events_userId_date ON events(userId, date);
CREATE INDEX idx_notifications_userId_isRead ON notifications(userId, isRead);
CREATE INDEX idx_chat_sessions_userId ON chat_sessions(userId);
CREATE INDEX idx_chat_history_sessionId ON chat_history(sessionId);
```

## ğŸ¤ Contributing

We welcome contributions from the community! Here's how you can help make StudyMateAI better:

### ğŸŒŸ Ways to Contribute

- ğŸ› Report bugs and issues
- ğŸ’¡ Suggest new features or enhancements
- ğŸ“ Improve documentation
- ğŸ”§ Submit pull requests
- ğŸ¨ Enhance UI/UX design
- ğŸŒ Add translations

### ğŸ“‹ Contribution Guidelines

1. **Fork the Repository**

   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/YourUsername/StudyMateAI.git
   cd StudyMateAI
   ```

2. **Create a Feature Branch**

   ```bash
   git checkout -b feature/AmazingFeature
   ```

3. **Make Your Changes**

   - Follow the existing code style
   - Write meaningful commit messages
   - Add tests for new features
   - Update documentation as needed

4. **Test Your Changes**

   ```bash
   # Backend tests
   cd backend && npm test

   # Frontend tests
   cd frontend && npm test
   ```

5. **Commit Your Changes**

   ```bash
   git add .
   git commit -m 'feat: Add some AmazingFeature'
   ```

   **Commit Message Convention:**

   - `feat:` New feature
   - `fix:` Bug fix
   - `docs:` Documentation changes
   - `style:` Code style changes (formatting)
   - `refactor:` Code refactoring
   - `test:` Adding tests
   - `chore:` Maintenance tasks

6. **Push to Your Fork**

   ```bash
   git push origin feature/AmazingFeature
   ```

7. **Open a Pull Request**
   - Provide a clear description of changes
   - Link related issues
   - Add screenshots for UI changes
   - Ensure all tests pass

### ğŸ” Code Review Process

1. Maintainer reviews the PR
2. Automated tests must pass
3. At least one approval required
4. Changes may be requested
5. Once approved, PR will be merged

### ğŸ“œ Code of Conduct

- Be respectful and inclusive
- Provide constructive feedback
- Focus on the code, not the person
- Help others learn and grow

### ğŸ› Reporting Bugs

When reporting bugs, please include:

- **Description**: Clear description of the issue
- **Steps to Reproduce**: Detailed steps
- **Expected Behavior**: What should happen
- **Actual Behavior**: What actually happens
- **Screenshots**: If applicable
- **Environment**:
  - OS: [e.g., Windows 11, macOS 14]
  - Node.js version
  - Browser version (for frontend issues)
  - Docker version (if applicable)

### ğŸ’¡ Feature Requests

When suggesting features:

- Describe the problem it solves
- Explain the proposed solution
- Provide examples or mockups
- Consider implementation complexity

### ğŸ“§ Questions?

- Open a [GitHub Discussion](https://github.com/YngJesus/StudyMateAI/discussions)
- Email: bahajedidi2016@gmail.com

